reviews.text: This location is favorite of mine Anthony the manger makes the best pizzas there. I am being loyal customer for life. The buffalo pizza the bbq pizza are all great but my favorite is the veggie. I like my pizza baked lightly so you can fold it over a well done crunchy pizza. Enjoy ready to eat slices or order a whole pie and eat. You can eat the whole pizza and you won‚Äôt feel sluggish that shows they use quality ingredients. The have great staff who keeps the place clean and friendly. They have tv with live sports or playing good movies. Be sure to tip them they go above beyond at this location.

Ordered a pizza and salad to go last week (on 4/12/24 around 5 pm) and while the pizza was fine, the salad had a bunch of mushy rotten pieces of spring mix in it, so gross. Won't be spending $13 for a salad there ever again!

I ordered a gluten free Brooklyn pizza from Flippin' and they sent me a burnt pizza! You guys can do better than that. If the pizza looks burnt, you should just remake it next time. The flavor was terrible as a result and I only ate half because I was hungry and had no other alternative.

Great single slice selection.  Vegetarian and carnivore options.  I had mine heated and the crust was perfectly crispy with a delicious sauce and toppings.  The server was friendly and checked in to see if all was well.  My first visit here and I saw that they do have vegan pizza options.  See pictures for more info.

Wow. Customer service here is off the charts. The pizza isn't bad either. An employee named Christian made our experience unforgettable. He was super nice, attentive, and gave us extra garlic knots because the other ones were over cooked in his mind. This is a star employer that is building a great reputation for Flippin pizza. I will return.

editorial_summary.overview: Branch of a chain offering New York-style thin-crust pizza with an array of toppings.

Some pizza places keep slices under heat lamps, but if the pizza sat for too long at unsafe temperatures (between 40‚Äì140¬∞F), bacteria like Bacillus cereus or Staphylococcus aureus could have started growing.

This is especially risky for meat toppings, which spoil faster, and I did in fact get a meat lovers pizza when I was there.

Reheating doesn‚Äôt kill the toxins that some bacteria produce, which in turn can cause food poisoning. Staphylococcus aureus or Bacillus cereus, can cause symptoms within 1‚Äì6 hours.

These bacteria produce toxins in food before you eat it, leading to rapid-onset nausea, vomiting, and diarrhea.

Bacillus cereus (common in starchy foods like pizza crust) and Staphylococcus aureus (often found in meat and dairy) produce toxins that reheating won‚Äôt destroy.

I hope your management can do a better job educating your staff and team as they deserve better than "educating" your customers.
